      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to use this"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Any platform that plans to support more than one vendor within 12 months."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "When you want to implement multi-vendor failover routing on top of a clean interface."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "When agents must be testable offline via a mock implementation of the interface."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How to implement"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Define the LLMClient abstract base class with the minimal set of methods."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Implement a concrete adapter for your primary vendor."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Replace all direct vendor SDK calls in agent code with LLMClient method calls."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add instrumentation in the base class or a decorator."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Implement a MockLLMClient for unit tests that returns deterministic canned responses."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add a second adapter for your secondary vendor and validate against your test suite."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Implementation example"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import abc, typing\n\nclass Message(typing.TypedDict):\n    role: str   # \"system\" | \"user\" | \"assistant\"\n    content: str\n\nclass LLMClient(abc.ABC):\n    \"\"\"Vendor-agnostic interface for language model calls.\"\"\"\n\n    @abc.abstractmethod\n    def complete(self, messages: list[Message], **kwargs) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Return the assistant response string.\"\"\"\n\n    @abc.abstractmethod\n    def complete_stream(self, messages: list[Message], **kwargs) -> typing.Iterator[str]:\n        \"\"\"Yield incremental response chunks.\"\"\"\n\n    @property\n    @abc.abstractmethod\n    def model_id(self) -> str: ...\n\n# OpenAI adapter\nclass OpenAIAdapter(LLMClient):\n    def __init__(self, client, model: str = \"gpt-4o\"):\n        self._client = client\n        self._model = model\n\n    @property\n    def model_id(self) -> str:\n        return self._model\n\n    def complete(self, messages: list[Message], **kwargs) -> str:\n        resp = self._client.chat.completions.create(\n            model=self._model, messages=messages, **kwargs\n        )\n        return resp.choices[0].message.content\n\n    def complete_stream(self, messages: list[Message], **kwargs) -> typing.Iterator[str]:\n        stream = self._client.chat.completions.create(\n            model=self._model, messages=messages, stream=True, **kwargs\n        )\n        for chunk in stream:\n            delta = chunk.choices[0].delta.content\n            if delta:\n                yield delta\n\n# Anthropic adapter\nclass AnthropicAdapter(LLMClient):\n    def __init__(self, client, model: str = \"claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022\"):\n        self._client = client\n        self._model = model\n\n    @property\n    def model_id(self) -> str:\n        return self._model\n\n    def complete(self, messages: list[Message], **kwargs) -> str:\n        system = next((m[\"content\"] for m in messages if m[\"role\"] == \"system\"), \"\")\n        user_msgs = [m for m in messages if m[\"role\"] != \"system\"]\n        resp = self._client.messages.create(\n            model=self._model, system=system, messages=user_msgs,\n            max_tokens=kwargs.get(\"max_tokens\", 4096),\n        )\n        return resp.content[0].text\n\n    def complete_stream(self, messages: list[Message], **kwargs) -> typing.Iterator[str]:\n        system = next((m[\"content\"] for m in messages if m[\"role\"] == \"system\"), \"\")\n        user_msgs = [m for m in messages if m[\"role\"] != \"system\"]\n        with self._client.messages.stream(\n            model=self._model, system=system, messages=user_msgs,\n            max_tokens=kwargs.get(\"max_tokens\", 4096),\n        ) as stream:\n            for text in stream.text_stream:\n                yield text\n\n# Mock for unit tests\nclass MockLLMClient(LLMClient):\n    def __init__(self, response: str = \"mock response\"):\n        self._response = response\n\n    @property\n    def model_id(self) -> str:\n        return \"mock-v1\"\n\n    def complete(self, messages: list[Message], **kwargs) -> str:\n        return self._response\n\n    def complete_stream(self, messages: list[Message], **kwargs) -> typing.Iterator[str]:\n        yield self._response\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Real-world example"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A healthcare AI platform built on a single vendor's SDK needed to add a HIPAA-compliant second vendor after a pricing change. Without an MAL, the migration required updating 23 agent files. After factoring out the abstraction, the same migration became a single new adapter file and a configuration change. The platform subsequently added a self-hosted open-source model for de-identified data without touching any agent code."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Over-designing the interface:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " avoid mapping every vendor capability; start with complete() and add methods only when needed."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Leaking vendor types:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " if vendor-SDK types appear outside adapters, the abstraction is broken."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "No contract tests:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " without a shared test suite all adapters must pass, adapters drift from the canonical interface over time."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Ignoring token counting:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " each vendor counts tokens differently; expose a count_tokens() method so agents can respect context windows."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best practices"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Write a parametrised contract test suite that runs against every adapter in CI."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Keep adapters in a dedicated package so vendor imports never bleed into agent code."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Instrument the base class: emit a span per complete() call with model_id, latency, and token counts."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Expose max_context_tokens to allow agents to trim retrieval results to the active vendor's window size."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Performance and scalability"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The abstraction layer itself adds no meaningful latency\u2014it is pure in-process method dispatch. The primary performance concern is streaming: ensure complete_stream() passes through chunks immediately without buffering, so time-to-first-token remains as low as the vendor provides. For high-throughput scenarios, the adapter should reuse the vendor SDK's connection pool rather than creating a new HTTP session per call."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Context window management across vendors"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Vendors have different context window sizes. A 200k-token window on vendor A versus a 32k window on vendor B changes how much context your agent can pass. Expose a max_context_tokens property on the interface so agent code can dynamically trim retrieval results to fit the window of whichever vendor the router selects. Without this, a failover from a large-context vendor to a small-context vendor will produce truncation errors that are hard to diagnose."
          }
        ]
      },
